I can see that `@Nullable` and `@Nonnull` annotations _could_ be helpful in preventing `NullPointerException`s but they do not propagate very far.

 - The effectiveness of these annotations drop off completely after one level of indirection, so if you only add a few they don&#39;t propagate very far. 
 - Since these annotations are not well enforced there is a danger of assuming a value marked with `@Nonnull` is not null and consequently not performing null checks. 

